<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-37-0600 </DOCNO><TEXT>A 1300 MW pressurized water reactor plant contains about 17 000 valves,some of which are safety-related and also important to plant availability.For experimental valve qualification, test stands for long-term and typetests, facilities for system transients including pipe breaks and equipmentfor in-situ testing at the plant are available. The following test programsare presented as examples: valve type qualification, qualification ofmain steam isolation valves to pipe break conditions, and in-situ diagnostictesting of valves in nuclear power plants.</TEXT></DOC>